title: Iki
text:
TWO THINGS:

Don't ever come and tell someone how much to tip you when there's no mandatory tip, but only suggestions like every other bill in this country. Especially when services are mediocre at best.

Secondly, don't ever add suggested tips on the total bill. It is always before taxes.

This is the FIRST ever restaurant I've been to in my life that comes back and asks for more tip, and the first one I've noticed that add their suggested tip box on the total after tax. Life is hard as it is already, don't scam people.

I was certainly surprised to say the least by that. Who on earth does that? WOW.

title: Iki
text:
Parking: There is a nearby parking lot for $3/hour (maximum of 3 hours). There is street/metered parking (difficult to find).

We discovered this place after deciding not to wait on the waitlist for Szechuan Mountain House.

Service: Service was good. We were greeted and seated immediately.

Atmosphere: I really liked the decor/ambiance. Really clean/modern look.

Food: The portion sizes were rather small and on the more expensive end. We ordered various dishes and the presentation of the food was great.

Abalone - This was good. Had a citrus taste to it. The price of this was discounted when we went (not sure if this will remain at a discounted price for future visits)

Dragon Maki - Tasted good but nothing above and beyond. Comparable to any other sushi restaurant.

Agedashi Tofu - This was good. Again, nothing above and beyond. Can get this anywhere and will be comparable.

Takoyaki - Underwhelming. The bottom of the ball appeared to be flat.

Tori Karaage - Underwhelming. Can get fried chicken anywhere.

Lava Stone A5 Wagyu - The meat was tender but was tasteless. Portion size was really small and definitely not worth the $36. Better off getting 2-3 more rolls instead of this.

Oyako Don - Underwhelming. Nothing stood out and you wont be missing out if you go anywhere else that offers this.

Seafood Yaki Udon - This was good. The sauce was good. It wasnt too oily. Definitely above average for udon.

Ice Cream - Complementary at the end. This was also good. Only had the options of matcha or vanilla.

Verdict: I would recommend coming here to try it out however this is definitely not the spot to go to if you are looking for dinner/something to fill you up. Place is more like a spot for lunch.

title: 1392 Seafood BBQ
text:
To start off, this place had a great vibe to it. If you were to go out with friends to this place, it‚Äôs great for a drinking atmosphere. The projectors project onto the walls some sort of images I don‚Äôt quite remember. It‚Äôs nicely lit inside with colorful blueish lights and other colors. The seating arrangement‚Äôs alright. title: 1392 Seafood BBQ
text: Heat up your taste buds at ‚Äô1392 Seafood BBQ‚Äò in Flushing, NY! This hidden gem is your passport to a world of savory Chinese-style BBQ and mouthwatering seafood dishes. During the holiday season, they have an amazing combo including a great mix seafood & lobster stew, an appetizer and a chicken skewers, which is only $99.99! Join me on this flavor-packed voyage and discover your new favorite dining spot!

title: Aroma Restaurant & Sushi Bar
text:
Aroma Restaurant & Sushi Bar menu outside the restaurant convinced us to go inside. Not Sushi eaters but the Teriyaki Chicken caught our eye.

Welp I hit my 600K now Can ya'll the original number goal I had in my head ????
Hint I didn't hit it yet....

@kendrickclone70 and I spent the day on some going to see our doctors to make sure our health is on point. And coming out one of our appointments we notice this restaurant across the street @aromarestaurantt which is listed Aroma Restaurant and Sushi Bar as we are reading the menu in the window. And the Teriyaki Chicken caught our eyes. So we pulled up.
As we are seated by a latin waitress with a nice size BBL I look around the restaurant and all the waitresses are latin with BBL's BBL's. Now I am wondering is BBL's mandatory for them to get a job there. We ordered both our Teriyaki Chicken and when they came out plated so nice. And the food was delicious. And what actually brings this restaurant over the top for me was not the BBL's and the abundance of latin woman.
The top for me was the simple glass of water. The water was a ice cold and even though it was in a cocktail glass our waitresses yes waitresses kept my glass refilled over and over and over. I added the lime and by the time I was finished eating my slow self lunch my mucous (pause) was no longer bothering me in my chest.
Health is wealth #2024

title: Aroma Restaurant & Sushi Bar
text: The restaurant serves great dishes - I usually get the penne a La vodka with shrimp but this time around I got the samba sushi roll , fried calamari and then for my main course lamb chops- oh my good samba roll was delicious- fried calamari was tender and not chewy - plus that marinara sauce was on the money - the lamb chops were great and I had that with tostones and grilled vegetables - my neice ordered the branzino fish in which I tried - everything was finger licking good- you won‚Äôt be disappointed- the service is wonderful - beautiful polite women- who tend to every need including water whenever I drank it down and I drink a lot of water - the atmosphere is relaxing and I would go there every week if I could afford it üòú but the prices are decent depending on what u get but please know that you won‚Äôt be waisting a dime on anything - it‚Äôs all worth it - highly recommend

title: Aroma Restaurant & Sushi Bar
text:
This place is definitely one of my favorites in NYCü•∞ü•∞üòçü§©üëèüèº... even when I visit other places in the city, I tend to finish my nights at this restaurant because of their music and their pretty affordable appetizers and drinks (which are good-good).

It's really weird to me to find mixed reviews over here, considering my friends, clients and myself never had an issue with them. I'd suggest you try these type of places by yourself, because you never know the two sides of a story.

Aroma has always delivered the best service no matter the crowd, the day nor the time. And I'm a regular there, so I know what I'm talking about.ü§ó

Overall, it is a safe and clean restaurant with great vibes and ambiance, their music selection is always fiiiirrreeee üî•üî•üî•üî• THE FOOD: absolutely delicious, and if your a wine lover üç∑, they have a wide variety of world renowned brands and amazingly good cocktails. Try the margaritas and the Passion Fruit juice, sooo good... Specially the tamarindo mojito and the Jumbo Rainbow margarita, one of those and you'll be set!

If you're into pasta, order their Penne a la Vodka, the lobster ravioli or their Seafood Fra Diavolo ü•∞. From the appetizers menu, I recommend the fried shumai, mofongo trios, the quesadilla, the Spring rolls, and finally the cheese and spinach empanadas.

Also, make sure to order sushi, IT'S THE BEST in the area! and actually one of the best in the city, for an unbeatable price. My favorite sushi rolls are "Nemo Roll" and "Aroma Roll" (those are a little spicy).

text: I finally got a chance to try this place out after passing by hundreds of times. It's a small space with about 8 tables, The menu is pretty extensive with all of the Mexican favorites you would expect complete with all the various meats you've come to love from Mexican cuisine. I had a hankering for tostadas and My elder came with tinga, which is spicy chicken. Tostadas are dry tortillas loaded with beans lettuce tomatoes maybe peppers, cheese and your choice of meat. The best thing about tostadas is that you have to eat them fresh because they tend to absorb the moisture from the food and can break apart in your hands. You eat them like you would eat a small pizza and I really enjoyed these tostadas. The service was very good and this place has been here a while and does a lot of takeout. It was well worth the wait. Highly recommended!!!

text: The food is excellent. Drinks are awesome. Prices are good too. The staff was awesome.

title: Home BX Steakhouse
text: I wish I would have read the reviews before coming here. I started off with the oysters and was disappointed at the texture and flavor to top off if your gonna serve oysters please serve it with condiments that are meant to go with it, who gives ketchup? I had ordered my steak rare and it was over cooked and not flavorful the peppercorn sauce was the bigger let down. As for the service horrible. We had to flag down our waitress multiple times to place our order and get our bill never bothered once to check in on how the meal was.  Only reason our drinks were refilled were because the bussers would be the ones to come over. Save your money far better places to eat in the Bronx than this one

title: Home BX Steakhouse
text: If you‚Äôre going to be a steak you must know how to cook steak! And this place unfortunately does not.  We ordered a Ny strip steak (medium) with mac cheese & truffle fires and a beef bourguignon. The steak was overcooked to well done and had no flavor, the mac was bland and they forgot the truffle fries even after the food came and we reminded them. As for the beef bourguignon the meat was tender and flavorful but it did not pair well with the pasta they serve it with. Although we did not enjoy the dinner we did enjoy the drinks and appetizers. We had the caesar salad, bacon & french onion soup, I love me some french onion soup and this one was good and their frida cocktail was delicious. As for the servers whom were friendly but not attentive, I had to ask for my server 3x to get a refill on our drinks which shouldn‚Äôt take an hour. Due to this experience I will not return nor do I recommend Home Bx Steakhouse.

title: Home BX Steakhouse
text: Our experience at BX Steakhouse was outstanding, thanks to Wendy's recommendation. Joselito, our server, provided attentive and professional service throughout the evening, ensuring that every aspect of our visit was enjoyable. The live music by Johnny Bliss added a nice touch to the atmosphere. Additionally, the drinks were expertly made and paired perfectly with our meal. Overall, we had a wonderful time and plan to return soon for another memorable dining experience.

title: Home BX Steakhouse
text: OK y'all this ones gonna be a long one. I am so so happy I found this lil hidden in plain sight gem! We went for bae's birthday and let me tell you this place did not disappoint! From when we walked in we were amazed at the instant vibe. It's a wonderful size restaurant and beautifully decorated. There were a few people but it was fairly empty and our waitress told us we could pick our own seats. We opted to sit as close to the fireplace area as possible. I mentioned to our wonderful waitress that it was bae's birthday and she smiled and winked at me. From beginning to end our waitress was perfect! She showed the right amount of attention to us without being overbearing and annoying. She took her time explaining the menu and drink menu. (We're always looking for the strongest drinks on the menu lol)The menu has something wonderful for every one's price range. I went with the lamb chops and brussel sprouts(y'all know how much I love the sprouts) bae went with the salmon and veggies with mashed potatoes. While waiting for our food the bartender came over with complimentary glasses of Rose(idk if they do that all the time so don't go there expecting it and being mad at me if they don't lol) and it was dry and delicious we were pleasantly shocked lol. Then the food came and everything was perfectly seasoned and phenomenal! They really show you love and take care of you in there! They have happy hour from 4-7 so needless to say we will def be checking that out very soon! While we were sitting and talking the waitress came by and asked if we wanted to take pictures by the piano(insert happy face) she even remembered it was his bday and brought him a complimentary piece of cheesecake which was also delish and sang him happy birthday all by herself. This place is a ten out of ten! Run don't walk to Home BX Steakhouse!

title: New Capitol
text:
I wanted to relax from the cool weather outside on my way home. So I went to New Capitol Restaurant. I ordered from here before, and I thank God that they serve breakfast dishes in the evening. So I ordered 1 French Toast Special (Scrambled Eggs, Bacon and Home Fries) and 1 Orange Juice. I ate breakfast for dinner comfortably in peace while watching television, something I haven‚Äôt done since the start of the digital age three years ago. It is wonderful how people can find new ways to connect by searching for opportunities online. I enjoyed the service, from the waiter serving me very friendly to the compassionate clerk by the entrance of the restaurant. I was about to take the glass with me by accident, but at least I was able to get the energy to go home.

On another evening, I stopped by to get the soup of the day. The waitress mentioned clam chowder, so I immediately ordered for the night. It was delicious. Good for the soul in the early winter days of the new year.

Thank you New Capitol!

text:

text: They used to have a location in Los Angeles, which I loved and missed when it closed. So happy to see it reopened in Flushing. Same great food: Coffee & Curry. Great combo and really modern Malaysian.

title: PappaRich
text:
We recently had lunch at Papa Rich in Flushing, a great spot for delicious Malaysian cuisine. My dad, who usually hesitates to try new places, found the restaurant very comfortable. He mentioned that the place was spacious and clean, creating an inviting and perfect atmosphere for a relaxing meal. He absolutely loved the Hainan Chicken with rice, praising its flavorful taste.

I opted for a trio of dishes: the flavorful Curry Chicken, the melt in your mouth Beef Rendang with perfectly cooked meat, and the Sambal Shrimp with a delicious and slightly sweet sauce.

title: PappaRich
text: This place is one of the few places to get authentic Halal Malaysian food that‚Äôs really good. The restaurant was extremely clean and the vibes are great. The waiters and kitchen staff was really kind and nice food came out clean and tasty. I‚Äôd rank it a solid B+ for the food not as good as I had in Malaysia, but I‚Äôd come back and invite my friends.

title: PappaRich
text: When we got to the place it was nice at first but things went downhill from there. We ordered the noodles with shrimp & fish cake which was very underwhelming because it looked good on the menu. After we finished, the lady who was serving us asked us to pay and I paid with card. I decided to not tip because I was low on money and I am a high school student. She got mad at me and kept asking about the tip. I genuinely felt bad because it‚Äôs not that I didn‚Äôt want to tip, I just couldn‚Äôt but she kept pressuring me. On the whole, my meal was edible yet underwhelming. My friend ordered the chicken and beef teriyaki with fried rice and two spring rolls. He loves teriyaki but  he's not a fan of their chicken and beef teriyaki. Being first-time patrons of The Yummy Kitchen, we felt blind-sided when the lady on the phone told me AFTER taking our food order that for FIRST-TIME customers they only accept cash or Apple Pay. This was not stated nor specified on their handout menu. On The Yummy Kitchen handout menu we'd received, it listed the credit cards that The Yummy Kitchen accepted: Visa, Mastercard, Discover. We were ready to pay for our meal with a credit card when the lady surprised me with the 'first-time customer/ cash/Apple Pay payment requirement'. We felt that was misleading and not in good faith. Needless to say, my friend and I will not be patronizing The Yummy Kitchen in the foreseeable future.

title: Kabul Kabob House
text:
The food is good but the service is disappointing and negligent. It's one of the best Afghan restaurants in Queens, their main entrees are plentiful and of good quality, but I would avoid their appetizers.

I came here with a friend on a weekday night, around 7:30 - 8:00 PM) and the restaurant was not busy and plenty of tables were available. When we asked if we could sit on a particular 4-seat table), we were told no because the restaurant may get busy later. That's understandable, but then it was given to another 2-person party a little while later, which was odd. It also took them a long time to take our order, when the restaurant wasn't very busy. I also had to get up every time I needed something (soda, napkins, utensils, dessert). The table next to us may have been having the same issue. They wanted drinks but no one helped them either - I ended up helping them get their sodas.

Although the food is fantastic, the service has a long way to go.

title: Che Li Flushing ÊµôÈáå | Authentic Chinese Restaurant
text:
I came here last year and returned a couple of weeks ago. I had a fantastic experience both times!
We didn't have a reservation so we had to wait for a bit, but despite being seated at a table away from the main area, the service was still very attentive and the food didn't take too long to come out.
We got the pork soup dumplings, crab meat tofu stew, Yangzhou meatball, and nine-spice rabbit. Their soup dumplings are my favorite in Flushing now that the quality at other well-known restaurants has declined, with fairly thin skin and lots of soup. The other dish that surprised us in a good way was the rabbit, the flavor was subtle but very aromatic.

We had wanted to try out their beggar's chicken but they told us they only make about a dozen a day and were sold out, so that's a perfect excuse for us to return soon!

title: El Economico
text: I have visited this business since my childhood. My uncles, parents, and all my relatives used to eat here after work or on their days off, either dining in or taking food home. We never had issues. The women working at the counter were always friendly, always smiling. The same when paying at the cash register. But I don't know, in recent years, they have changed ownership, I suppose, and the staff as well, leading to a drastic change. The people there, especially those working at the front, always seem busy. That's not the problem. The issue is their attitude. They look at you with complete disdain if you're not from their country. And even though I'm of a white complexion, it's not that big of a deal, but just for not being Dominican, I would say, they have a very arrogant attitude. And if one complains to the person at the cash register, total support, I think they cover for each other. The customer service is terrible, terrible, terrible. How do they expect someone to give them a tip with such an attitude? And they don't just expect it, they demand it, that's the worst part. I'm giving it one star because that's what it asks for, but honestly, this business doesn't even deserve one star. Moreover, people are even drinking at the counter. That never happened before. This business is going to fall soon. I'm warning my family and friends not to go to this place because the people are rude. Lately, I've noticed that the food is coming out disgusting. Zero, zero stars, I would say for this restaurant.

title: Smashburger
text:
The service is decent and the space clean.  The music is a little loud, I couldn't imagine wanting to sit here and chat on a date.  I guess that's why the place isn't too packed on a sunny afternoon.
Anyhow on to the important part: the food.

The burgers are overcooked to well done, greasy, and flavorless! If they're seasoned, I couldn't tell- they were so bland. And the tots were too crispy and oily. I attached a photo of the oil left behind. The bottom is where the tots were.  At the end I was left with an oily after taste, and a slight allergic reaction- I think the burger had mayo, which I don't eat often.  But I had mayo last week, and didn't have the same reaction.
If you want an over-priced greasy burger- still don't come here.  You can get a better overpriced burger someplace else.

I should also add that someone let their half-eaten burger behind on another table- which I wish I saw before ordering.  It looked like a heap of uninspired disappointment in a bun.

title: Double Dragon
text: I have been ordering my meals from Double dragon for 10 years. Always get delivery. The food has always been fresh, and hot. The Dragon has always prepared my orders exactly how I wanted. No veggies,xtra onion and bean sprouts,no soy sauce only duck sauce etc.. Well this evening I ordered my favorite egg foo yung and I asked for the egg too be cooked well so it wouldn‚Äôt be soggy. My favorite delivery man came and when I started to prepare my plate the egg was super soft and soggy. Called n spoke to the manager and they sent me another order but the second order was even worse and it had a weird taste and thin hard black pieces like burnt bones. I appreciate the fact that the manager and the staff tried to make things right but in my opinion they need to get rid of this chef because the  chef that was there b4 made the best food ever.No matter what I ordered it was always fresh and cooked to perfection.

title: Picante Picante
text: After the first time I tried the Picante, I knew I was going to be going back very often! I come from New Jersey so you can understand how great the food must be if I‚Äôm always going into the city to either dine in or do take out. The service is great, the waitresses are always very attentive and often help me decide what to eat since there is so many options that sound so delicious! The male manager has given me great recommendations and has been very helpful if I ever had even a slight issue with an order. The food is always fast, warm, and very tasty. (Not to mention they have GREAT portions at a price you really can‚Äôt beat!!) It‚Äôs usually pretty hard to order because everything sounds SO SO SO GOOD!  Every time I go it is always very clean and you are likely to see either the manager or a server cleaning up extra things in the little bit of free time they have, in between tables and orders. They always go above and beyond to make sure their customers are happy, satisfied, and leave with full bellies! The environment is very family friendly. I have seen them accommodate big parties of families and friends which is so nice to know. For the atmosphere they have gorgeous paintings on the wall with lots of detail and it‚Äôs so nice they always decorate for the holidays! It‚Äôs a very family friendly place and I would HIGHLY recommend you go for your next breakfast, lunch, or dinner!

title: Tin Mar√≠n Tapas
text:
One of my favorite places in NYC.
Food, Service and Ambience are always amazing here.
Live music from local artist Thursday to Sunday.

The secret to the success of this establishment is the staff. They are hard working, attentive, and always make you feel welcomed, like family. Bartenders usually know what you are drinking when you come back the 3rd time and are always quick to serve, even when there is no space at the bar. In the kitchen is the matriarch, Mama Henry, the Owners mother. She makes every sauces, flan, beans, and many more items from scratch.

Happy Hours are from open to 7:00PM on weekdays, their sangria, margaritas are strong and on point and come in many fresh fruit flavors.

Some must haves on the tapas are the empanadas, mofonguitos, pulpo, tostones and chorizo, bacon wrapped dates, canastitas de bacalao, for mains the churrasco, paella and salmon are amazing.

I used to bartend here for 6 years and I never once was tired of the food, this place is like family to me.

Truly a neighborhood gem.

Their tapas (I recommend the Lamb chops) are amazing and the Churrasco is mouth watering. The young ladies behind the bar were quick to remember my signature drink (The Nestor) & thats always a good sign of attentiveness. Topping things off is the great live music Thursday-Sunday.
Whenever in the area or not‚Ä¶ swing by‚Ä¶ you‚Äôll be happy you did!

title: Tobala
text: The service here is top notch. My wife and I sat at the bar. We weren't that hungry so the portions here were perfect and I was way more interested in the bar. We sat at the bar and our servers were very gracious. They created a mezcal flight for me based on my little knowledge of mezcal, my alcoholic preferences, and what dishes we ordered. $48 for a mezcal flight, 3 servings from 3 different bottles. Each one was very different from the last. My wife had a non alcoholic drink, La Orgua. I took a sip. It was a very mild flavored drink. Looked beautiful but tasted watered down. We ordered the guacamole which came from cotija cheese on top. The guac serving was generous and delicious. The aguachiles were Oaxacan style. I've had aguachiles in Mexico City so I was foolishly expecting a different flavor so I did not enjoy that much. Nothing wrong with the dish but I felt the seasoning was lacking. Still a generous portion. Both dishes served with tostadas. I'll definitely be back for mezcal and to try cocktails.

title: Tobala
text:
I feel taken advantage of, robbed even.

My friend and I went to Tobal√° to have the Valentine prefixe menu. We reserved our table via Resy, and paid a non-refundable deposit of $50 EACH, which they stated would go towards the overall tab at the end of the night.

Our reservation was for 7pm, yet we were seated at a bit after 7:30pm, and did not receive our first course until 8:30. The wait time in-between courses was ridiculous and every dish was more mediocre than the last. The staff was pretty nice whenever they stopped by our table, but that was a rare occurrence in itself.

When it was time to pay, they did not include the $100 we had already put towards the bill until we informed them. And when asked to split the bill in half between two cards, they ended up putting 1/3 on one card and 2/3 of the bill on the other.

I would not come back, and definitely not recommend. I was looking forward to visiting this new addition to the Riverdale area, and really sad that this was the experience we got. Truly baffled.
Overall we spent $300 on an unimaginative and tasteless meal.
